# Field

A layout that pairs a form control with its label, description, and message.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("email")], [html.text("Email")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("email"),
      attribute.type_("email"),
      attribute.placeholder("ada@glow.dev"),
    ]),
    field.description([], [
      html.text("We'll only contact you about your account."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add field
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([attribute.class("w-64")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("display-name")], [html.text("Display name")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("display-name"),
      attribute.placeholder("Ada Lovelace"),
    ]),
    field.description([], [
      html.text("Shown on your profile and next to your comments."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Examples

Pair any control with a label and description, group related fields, and surface validation errors.

### Text Field

Stack a label, text field, and description inside a field with the vertical attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-64")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("username")], [html.text("Username")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("username"),
      attribute.placeholder("ada"),
    ]),
    field.description([], [html.text("Lowercase letters and underscores.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Text Area

Capture multi-line input in a text area with the vertical attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_area

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.vertical(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("feedback")], [html.text("Feedback")]),
    text_area.input(
      [
        attribute.id("feedback"),
        attribute.placeholder("Tell us what you think..."),
      ],
      "",
    ),
    field.description([], [
      html.text("Share anything that would make Drip better."),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Checkbox

Set a checkbox inline with its label using the horizontal attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/checkbox
import ui/field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.horizontal(), attribute.class("w-72")], [
    checkbox.input([
      attribute.id("email-notifications"),
      attribute.checked(True),
    ]),
    field.content([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("email-notifications")], [
        html.text("Email notifications"),
      ]),
      field.description([], [
        html.text("Send a digest of activity once per week."),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Switch

Pair a switch with an inline label using the horizontal attribute.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/switch

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([field.horizontal(), attribute.class("w-fit")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("reduced-motion")], [
      html.text("Reduced motion"),
    ]),
    switch.input([
      attribute.id("reduced-motion"),
      attribute.checked(True),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Radio Group

Nest horizontal fields inside a radio group so each option pairs with a field label.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/radio_group

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.set([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.legend([attribute.id("subscription-plan-legend")], [
      html.text("Subscription plan"),
    ]),
    field.description([], [
      html.text("Yearly and lifetime plans offer the biggest savings."),
    ]),
    radio_group.root([attribute.aria_labelledby("subscription-plan-legend")], [
      field.root([field.horizontal()], [
        radio_group.item([
          attribute.id("plan-monthly"),
          attribute.name("subscription-plan"),
          attribute.value("monthly"),
          attribute.checked(True),
        ]),
        field.label([attribute.for("plan-monthly")], [html.text("Monthly")]),
      ]),
      field.root([field.horizontal()], [
        radio_group.item([
          attribute.id("plan-yearly"),
          attribute.name("subscription-plan"),
          attribute.value("yearly"),
        ]),
        field.label([attribute.for("plan-yearly")], [html.text("Yearly")]),
      ]),
      field.root([field.horizontal()], [
        radio_group.item([
          attribute.id("plan-lifetime"),
          attribute.name("subscription-plan"),
          attribute.value("lifetime"),
        ]),
        field.label([attribute.for("plan-lifetime")], [html.text("Lifetime")]),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Radio Card

Wrap a field root in a label to turn each option into a selection card.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/radio_group

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.set([attribute.class("w-80")], [
    field.legend([], [html.text("Compute environment")]),
    field.description([], [html.text("Choose where your GPU workloads run.")]),
    field.group([], [
      field.label([], [
        field.root([field.horizontal()], [
          field.content([], [
            field.title([], [html.text("Kubernetes")]),
            field.description([], [
              html.text("Run GPU workloads on a managed K8s cluster."),
            ]),
          ]),
          radio_group.item([
            attribute.id("env-kubernetes"),
            attribute.name("compute-environment"),
            attribute.value("kubernetes"),
            attribute.checked(True),
          ]),
        ]),
      ]),
      field.label([], [
        field.root([field.horizontal()], [
          field.content([], [
            field.title([], [html.text("Virtual machine")]),
            field.description([], [
              html.text("Spin up a dedicated VM with direct GPU access."),
            ]),
          ]),
          radio_group.item([
            attribute.id("env-vm"),
            attribute.name("compute-environment"),
            attribute.value("vm"),
          ]),
        ]),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Invalid

Set aria-invalid on the control and add a field error element to surface validation errors.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("work-email")], [html.text("Work email")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("work-email"),
      attribute.type_("email"),
      attribute.value("not-an-email"),
      attribute.aria_invalid("true"),
    ]),
    field.error([], [html.text("Enter a valid email address.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Required

Mark the control required and the surrounding label will surface an accent asterisk.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("full-name")], [html.text("Full name")]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("full-name"),
      attribute.required(True),
      attribute.placeholder("Ada Lovelace"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Disabled

Disable the control with the disabled attribute to block input and dim the surrounding label.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.root([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.label([attribute.for("workspace-handle")], [
      html.text("Workspace handle"),
    ]),
    text_field.input([
      attribute.id("workspace-handle"),
      attribute.value("acme"),
      attribute.disabled(True),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Group

Wrap several fields in a field group for consistent spacing and a shared container query.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.group([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.root([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("first-name")], [html.text("First name")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("first-name"),
        attribute.placeholder("Ada"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.root([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("last-name")], [html.text("Last name")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("last-name"),
        attribute.placeholder("Lovelace"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.root([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("email-address")], [html.text("Email")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("email-address"),
        attribute.type_("email"),
        attribute.placeholder("ada@glow.dev"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Set & Legend

Bind related fields under a field set with a legend.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.set([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.legend([], [html.text("Workspace")]),
    field.description([], [
      html.text("Shown wherever your workspace appears."),
    ]),
    field.group([], [
      field.root([], [
        field.label([attribute.for("display-name")], [
          html.text("Display name"),
        ]),
        text_field.input([
          attribute.id("display-name"),
          attribute.placeholder("Acme Inc"),
        ]),
      ]),
      field.root([], [
        field.label([attribute.for("handle")], [
          html.text("Workspace handle"),
        ]),
        text_field.input([
          attribute.id("handle"),
          attribute.placeholder("acme"),
        ]),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

### Separator

Drop a field separator between fields to break a form into sections. Pass children to render a centered label.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/field
import ui/text_field

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  field.group([attribute.class("w-72")], [
    field.root([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("current-password")], [
        html.text("Current password"),
      ]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("current-password"),
        attribute.type_("password"),
        attribute.placeholder("Enter current password"),
      ]),
    ]),
    field.separator([], [html.text("then")]),
    field.root([], [
      field.label([attribute.for("new-password")], [html.text("New password")]),
      text_field.input([
        attribute.id("new-password"),
        attribute.type_("password"),
        attribute.placeholder("At least 8 characters"),
      ]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Orientation Attributes

Three orientation attributes for the field root, one per layout. Pass one into the root's attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `field.vertical()` | Label stacked above the control; the default when no orientation attribute is set. |
| `field.horizontal()` | Label inline beside the control. |
| `field.responsive()` | Vertical until the parent field group reaches a minimum width, then horizontal. |

### Elements

Composition slots used inside a field root.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `field.root(attrs, children)` | The field root. |
| `field.label(attrs, children)` | Renders a label bound to a control via the for attribute. |
| `field.title(attrs, children)` | Heading for a field whose wrapping label already binds the control, as in a checkbox or radio card. |
| `field.description(attrs, children)` | Helper text rendered below the control. |
| `field.error(attrs, children)` | Validation message with role="alert". |
| `field.content(attrs, children)` | Wraps a label and description in a horizontal field. |
| `field.group(attrs, children)` | Stacks fields with consistent spacing. |
| `field.set(attrs, children)` | Wrapper that binds related fields together for screen readers. |
| `field.legend(attrs, children)` | Native legend, sized for section headings. |
| `field.legend_label(attrs, children)` | Native legend, sized to match a field label. |
| `field.separator(attrs, children)` | Horizontal divider between fields. Children render as a centered label over the line. |

### Attributes

Standard Lustre attributes the field responds to. Pass them on the inner control or label.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `attribute.for("id")` | On field label, binds the label to the control's id. |
| `attribute.required(True)` | On the inner control, surfaces an accent asterisk on the surrounding label. |
| `attribute.aria_invalid("true")` | On the inner control, surfaces its error ring; pair with a field error to announce the validation message. |
| `attribute.disabled(True)` | On the inner control, dims the surrounding label. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the field's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="field"]` | A field root. |
| `[data-orientation="vertical\|horizontal\|..."]` | The field root, tagged with its active orientation. |
| `[data-slot="field-label"]` | A field label or title. |
| `[data-slot="field-required"]` | The accent asterisk surfaced when a control is required. |
| `[data-slot="field-description"]` | The helper text below the control. |
| `[data-slot="field-error"]` | The validation message. |
| `[data-slot="field-content"]` | The label/description block in a horizontal field. |
| `[data-slot="field-group"]` | A group wrapper, also the container-query root. |
| `[data-slot="field-set"]` | The native fieldset wrapper. |
| `[data-slot="field-legend"]` | The native legend. |
| `[data-variant="legend\|label"]` | The legend, tagged for section heading vs label sizing. |
| `[data-slot="separator"][data-variant="field"]` | A separator between groups of fields. |

## Accessibility

**Native semantics, screen reader ready.** Field roots carry role="group" so the label, control, and helper text announce as one unit, and field error carries role="alert" so validation is announced the moment it appears. Bind each control to its field label with a matching for attribute, and group related controls in a field set with a field legend.

